      "id":"fashion/fashion-blog/2013/oct/16/man-buns-hair-trend-jake-gyllenhaal",
      "sectionId":"fashion",
      "sectionName":"Fashion",
      "webPublicationDate":"2013-10-16T15:31:00Z",
      "webTitle":"Man buns: a hair-raising trend",
      "webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/fashion/fashion-blog/2013/oct/16/man-buns-hair-trend-jake-gyllenhaal",
      "apiUrl":"http://content.guardianapis.com/fashion/fashion-blog/2013/oct/16/man-buns-hair-trend-jake-gyllenhaal",
      "fields":{
        "trailText":"<p><strong>Lauren Cochrane: </strong>David Beckham did it years ago, Harry Styles and Bradley Cooper are fans, Jake Gyllenhaal is the latest disciple – and YouTube will show you how. Meet the man bun</p>",
        "headline":"Man buns: a hair-raising trend",
        "body":"<p>Male hair trends can usually be traced back to – or blamed on – a single celebrity. The return of the short back and sides <a href=\"http://www.theguardian.com/fashion/2013/sep/03/gareth-bale-hair-real-madrid\" title=\"\">is Gareth Bale's doing</a>, while it's Zayn Malik's fault that so many teens and twentysomething men currently resemble cartoon hedgehogs. The origins of the latest trend, though, are less clean-cut – which is appropriate. Meet <a href=\"http://www.tumblr.com/tagged/man-bun\" title=\"\">the man bun</a>.</p><p>Not to be confused with a Sikh topknot – too high on the head – or a lazy musician's ponytail, the man bun is halfway between the two, like a scruffy Sumo twist. Hair is scraped straight back from the forehead and tied into a little bun just below the crown of the head, with the rest often hanging lose. The effect? A sort of makeshift undercut.</p><p>A growing trend, the man bun cannot be blamed on any one culprit, but <a href=\"http://www.theguardian.com/film/2013/sep/21/jake-gyllenhaal-prisoners-donnie-darko\" title=\"\">Jake Gyllenhaal</a> is its latest disciple. He was spotted on the set of his new movie Nightcrawlers <a href=\"http://www.buzzfeed.com/lyapalater/jake-gyllenhaal-is-a-man-with-a-bun\" title=\"\">sporting a fine man bun</a>. Others have preceded him – One Direction's <a href=\"http://www.theguardian.com/fashion/shortcuts/2013/aug/21/harry-styles-makeup-for-men-one-direction\" title=\"\">Harry Styles</a> and Leonardo di Caprio included. Andy Carroll – one of the few footballers since David Seaman's 90s heyday to still go for flowing tresses – dates the trend to Euro 2012, and David Beckham <a href=\"http://www.theguardian.com/football/gallery/2013/may/17/david-beckham-hairstyles-pictures\" title=\"\">obviously did it yonks ago</a>. But it's probably Bradley Cooper who has become this year's <a href=\"http://www.buzzfeed.com/lyapalater/bradley-coopers-bun-is-back\" title=\"\">patron saint of the man bun</a>. He's been wearing his pretty consistently since May, sometimes even freestyling with two for a mohican-meets-bunches effect.</p><p>While that might only be advisable for the experienced man-bun wearer, the classic version could be coming to a male near you soon. In real life. There are several YouTube \"how to\" videos up – <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=gFmHYukht3g\" title=\"\">one with nearly 100,000 views</a> – and they are already all over east London, an area that has  become the frontline for a look that could be described as part woodcutter, part obscure conceptual artist. Sophie Tok, co-owner of <a href=\"http://www.tommyguns-shoreditch.com\" title=\"\">hair salon Tommyguns in Shoreditch, east London</a>, believes the trend started in around 2010, \"when the 90s undercut came back. Guys wear them with beards and tattoos.\" For Tok, at the coalface of experimental hair in east London, \"they're over – a low undercut is coming in, shaving the hair into a triangular point at the back.\" While that could have most of the male population running for the hills, it's a sure sign the man bun has reached a tipping point for the mainstream. Households with hair elastics for both genders are only a matter of time.</p><!-- Guardian Watermark: internal-code/content/420160028|2013-10-17T12:53:06Z|d4d764cd94e735a9cd401d1c0d289a1751c36fd1 -->",
